	abstract = {The ice nucleating properties of a number of organic compounds have been investigated. Although many of these lacked the ability to nucleate ice, others showed high activities especially when prepared from melts. Two classes of compounds, steroids and substituted fluorenes were found to include a number of highly active compounds with onset temperatures in the range -2.5°C–5°C. Compounds lacking hydrogen bonding groups were inactive.

